Calling all Warriors, we have a Warrior family in need.

Over the holiday weekend a pipe burst in the home of one of our families. They are in urgent need of someplace to live while repairs are being made. They are a family of 7, 3 children and 4 adults.

If you or someone you know can help, please let me know. We understand that this is a difficult time for everyone, so let's do what we do best.... work together to help one of our own.

Thank you,

Miss Jezuit

Dear Parents & Guardians,
If you are looking for something for the kids to do, please take a look at Lacawac Sanctuary Virtual Learning Center.
Lacawac is located in Lake Ariel. We have taken our students on field trips to their environmental education center. Students had the opportunity to explore animal habitats, animal adaptations, and watersheds.
Students can choose to go on a virtual field trip, watch and listen to a nature story, or participate in a Forest Friday activity.
Feel free to share what you learned!
https://www.lacawac.org/virtual-learning-center.html

Take care!
Mrs. Wagner

post_text:
Dear Parents and Guardians,

Hang in there! You are all doing a great job in getting the school work done and to the teachers! Way to go Warriors!

I saw an article yesterday that stated that Secretary of Education Pedro Rivera said we should be coming back to school in the fall. I am sure many of you saw it as well. I have not received confirmation of that from him or the Governor's Office as of this email. Once I know something definitive, I will let you know. Keep your fingers crossed!!

Hope is alive and well!! We will be back together again, better than ever, stronger than ever and ready to take anything on!!

Miss Walsh

post_text:
From the Desk of Miss Walsh

Happy Wednesday!

I have a homework assignment for you today (not the children).....find 3 to 5 minutes (even if you have to lock yourself in the car!) to take time to breathe deeply and find a few things to be grateful for, it will help with your mental health and give you positive things to think about.

The staff and I are very grateful for you and all that you are doing. We continue to be honored by the level of support you offer to your children and to us! We are grateful for you!! The positive emails and the funny pictures are what get us through our days of missing you and your children!

Be safe!

Miss Walsh

post_text:
From the Desk of Miss Walsh...

Happy Tuesday!

Thank you for all the positive comments and great feedback on what we sent out yesterday!

I want to acknowledge the hard work being done by our teachers. They are fabulous teachers!

Now moving to videos, packets, etc. and not having faces in front of them is hard on them as well; they are adjusting too. I have asked them to do a 180 degree change on how they teach. No one could be prepared to go from live teaching to this..... It's challenging, all the way around. I believe that for a first shot at teaching "like this" they have done a great job!! As usual, when asked to do something for our students, they always say yes and do their individual best to contribute!

Remember to pace your teaching and learning; you have 7 days!

Stay safe Warriors and enjoy this beautiful day.

Miss Walsh

post_text:
From the Desk of Miss Walsh

Happy Monday Warriors,

Here are some important updates:

1. Lunch reminder: Monday/Wed/Thurs only, 11:00am-1:00pm. Started this week.
2. This week you will get a note from me about changes we are making to our Enrichment & Review plan. We will be moving toward a plan for learning that will include for you, a schedule of material, both new and review.
3. Remember to complete your Census 2020! It is imperative to get that done.
4. Our last day of "school" will still be June 8th. The Governor has approved us sticking to our original plan.
5. We have no plans yet for K or 8 graduations. When we know more, I will let you know.

Have a peace-filled day!

Miss Walsh

The answer to Wednesday's...what was Miss Walsh up to....I was at the elevator. Good eyes and funny guesses!!

Today....no picture challenge, just the picture of the hard working flowers!

Enjoy and have a peace-filled, colorful, beautiful and healthy weekend!

Miss Walsh

From the Desk of Miss Walsh

I apologize for being late today, with getting this out....it's busy here at school today!!

What was Miss Walsh up to yesterday.....I was peeking around the building from the side entrance to the parking lot!! Good eyes spies on that one! Today's challenge is attached.

Today, I have only ONE update regarding lunches:

Starting next week, April 20th, we are going to serve the "grab & go" lunches on Monday, Wednesday and Thursday only. Monday you will get lunch, Tuesday breakfast, Tuesday lunch and Wednesday breakfast. Wednesday you will get Wednesday lunch, Thursday breakfast. Thursday you will get Thursday lunch, and Friday breakfast and lunch, and Monday breakfast. We will not be serving "grab & go" lunches on Tuesdays and Fridays. I am doing this to limit the exposure of our staff who have been diligently here for the last 4 weeks. I hope you understand.

Be well, stay safe, wash those hands and REACH OUT TO LOVED ONES!!!

Miss Walsh

post_text:
Good Morning!

The challenge of what is is Miss Walsh up to...for yesterday, was: at the water cooler in Miss Jezuit's office!! Good eye-spy Warriors!! Today's challenge is attached!!

Although I have nothing new to report, I do have a few reminders....

My reminders are simple: keep washing those hands, stay positive (we are one week through this!), stay connected by making phone calls, sending letters and reaching out to people who you have not chatted with in a while. Enjoy this family time together, play games, and go for walks.

I have decided that every day I am going to research something that I have often wondered about and never had the time to research or read about. Today, my curiosity has lead me to dig into Mount Rushmore: who designed it, how long did it take to finish, how did the presidents get chosen? I am sure that I learned this some please along the line...but now I am curious. I encourage you to use this time to dig into what makes you curious!!

Have a peace-filled day!

Miss Walsh

post_text:
Parents, Guardians and Friends,

As you continue to send letters to Governor Wolf, Secretary of Education Pedro Rivera, and our local representatives in Harrisburg, I thought I'd share this level of hypocrisy (in my Principal opinion):

This past Saturday in the Scranton Times, on the front page, was the attached picture of Governor Wolf planning for the COVID -19 Virus in schools.

His suggestion is that we may have to teach our students at home! So therefore, isn't his plan for teaching at home just another name for cyber charter schooling??

His actions/reactions to COVID-19 reminds me of the story of Rudolph the Red Nosed Reindeer. Rudolph was treated very poorly, even purposely ostracized (just like charter schools) until he was needed to guide the sleigh when no one else could (just like charter schools). Rudolph succeeded and went down in history! I guess we just have to continue to do what we , as charter schools do; SUCCEED!

Miss Walsh

post_text:
The UNLESS contest is in full swing here at Fell Charter!

As most of you know, we send snacks home each week. In an effort to be more eco-friendly, we have been making an attempt to stop using plastic grocery bags. As of a month ago, we eliminated the need for almost all plastic bags and were just using 25.

On Tuesday of last week I challenged Natalie, Erika, and Lexi to find a way to send home 25 snack bags in a recyclable bag. On Thursday they come up with an idea. On Friday there were 25 bags made from recycled newspaper on my desk ready to go!

-Miss Jezuit

#fellcharterwarriors
#fcswarriorpride
#fcskidsgottalent
#fcskidscare
#isntitamazingwhatclevergirlscando

The kids loved listening to the Veteran‚Äôs stories, and even got an opportunity to do a little caroling! Such an AMAZING day!

- Mrs. McGurgan

Dear Warrior Family,

This year we are making some changes to our celebration of our Veterans!

Our students have been very lucky to have had so many amazing experiences with Veterans coming in to meet with them, share their stories and talk about what giving back really means. This year, we are going to send our students out into the Veterans community to give back and show our appreciation for all they have done to defend our freedom.

This community service opportunity will give our students a chance to give back to the local heroes and heroines who have given so much to us.

We will be sending more information, on how you can help, in the next few days.

post_text:
Today in Computer Science both 4th and 8th grade students completed an unplugged activity. Students needed to work together in small groups to define the the problem presented then prepare and plan a solution. Student groups were then instructed to design and create a rescue boat (made of tinfoil) that could hold as many people (glass beads) as possible without sinking. Students were excited to try out their boat and pleasantly surprised to find out that most of their boats were able to hold more ‚Äòpeople‚Äô than they predicted!

SHOUT OUT to Mrs. Wagner and Mr. Flanagan for teaching this amazing lesson today!

#fcscomputerscience #fellcharterschool #fellcharterwarriors

The teachers started back to school Wednesday and have been hard at work getting ready for the students. Friday, we all hopped in our cars and had ‚ÄúField Trip Friday‚Äù. We visited the University of Scranton, Everhart Museum, Center for Independent Living, and Steamtown National Historic Site. Everyone got some amazing ideas for planning field trips with a purpose for the upcoming school year.

Shout out to Mrs. Wagner for putting this amazing day together for us!

Thank you to everyone we met throughout the day for your kindness and hospitality. We truly appreciate it and cannot wait to bring our students back to learn from you as well!

post_text:
From the Desk of Miss Walsh...

Happy Wednesday!

My big news for this week, is that the Annual Parent Survey is coming home today with the oldest child in each family!

For our new families, this is our annual "check up" to see how we are doing! I ask that you reflect on our year so far and tell us what you think.
The data is collected, shared with the Board, and used for planning with the staff for the 2019-2020 school year.

I thank you in advance for your help with this!!!

Also, on behalf of myself and the Staff, we wish you a peace-filled holiday weekend!

Miss Walsh

post_text:
I apologize for the 2 hour delay call today, that was late. I can only act based on information when I receive it. I was not notified until late that side and back roads of Carbondale were icy, due to run off.
I need to thank the early drivers who are out checking the roads for OUR children's safety. They make every effort to get out there, check the roads and report conditions!
Please know that my intent is not to frustrate parents/guardians, but to act as quickly as I can once I have accurate information.
I know that we are all frustrated by the recent rounds of delays and cancellations. Please hang in there with me, we are almost to spring!

Miss Walsh

Today we invite you to join us in celebrating one of our students.

Recently, someone posted inappropriate comments on the school's Instagram page. Almost immediately Thomas, 6th grade, jumped in to defend the school.

Thomas, we are so very proud of the actions you took to stand up to this person. You stepped up and demonstrated what everyone should do in a situation like this... you stood up for what you believed in. This is something that we hope that all of our students would do when faced with adversity. Today we celebrate you!

HAPPY THOMAS DAY!

Have any dried out markers at home just sitting around? Looking for a way to dispose of them without harming the environment? Crayola has a program called Crayola ColorCycle that allows schools to do just that! They accept all brands of markers, dry erase markers, and highlighters that have dried out.

There is a drop box at the school in Mrs. Seymour‚Äôs classroom. Feel free to send in what you have. Help us help the environment!

#warriorpride #warriorsgiveback

Luis, we have watched you grow from a young 10 year old with everything to learn, to a 23 year old man with everything to teach. Six of our Middle School students are traveling to Harrisburg for the Cyber Robotics Coding Competition finals tomorrow. Fell Charter School will have two of our students competing. The other four, along with Miss Walsh, Mrs. Wagner, and Mrs. Seymour, will be there to cheer them on as they compete.

CRCC has decided to livestream the event! If you are interested in watching this to cheer on our amazing students, I provided the link below.

We want to wish our students the best of luck in the competition. We are all very proud of you.... you got this!

Click the link below during the competition and see our students coding live starting with Phase 1 at 9:45am, Phase 2 at 11:45am, and the post-competition Awards Ceremony will follow at 1:00pm.

post_text:
Fell Charter Middle School students Thomas, Alice, Bruce, Mason, Erika, and Jayson recently participated in a cyber coding club run by Mrs. Wagner. During this time they participated in a Cyber Robotics Coding Challenge that was open to all schools across the state. Out of 104 schools, our little school placed 17th AND 2 of our 6 students qualified to participate in a competition in Harrisburg!

On December 4th, our students will be traveling to the state capitol with Miss Walsh, Mrs. Wagner, and Mrs. Seymour for the competition. Alice and Bruce will be competing in the CRCC finals!

We are so unbelievably proud of all of you!

#warriorpride #fcsproud #crccfinals #harrisburgherewecome
